<!-- CURSOR_SUMMARY -->
---

> [!NOTE]
> **Medium Risk**
> Introduces a new transcript compaction/export path and changes transcript serialization to always include timestamps, which could affect downstream consumers expecting the previous JSONL shape.
> 
> **Overview**
> Adds support for the `compact_transcript` capability by introducing a new `compact-transcript` subcommand that reads a JSONL transcript, converts supported `user`/`assistant` entries into a versioned compact JSONL format (including agent + CLI version metadata), and returns it base64-encoded.
> 
> Updates transcript handling to include `timestamp` on transcript lines (and writes RFC3339 timestamps in the `roger-roger` CLI), and adds tests covering compact conversion, error cases, and base64 encoding behavior.
